    <h2 id="faq">FAQ: Collagen and Vitamin C</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Should you take vitamin C with collagen?</summary><p>Yes — essential cofactor. 70-100mg daily. Your body cannot build new collagen without it.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much vitamin C with collagen?</summary><p>70-100mg daily. Most premium collagen gummies include 30-60mg; diet fills the rest.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>When should I take vitamin C with collagen?</summary><p>Same time. Morning with breakfast is optimal. Peptides need C in circulation when they reach the dermis.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Does vitamin C help absorption?</summary><p>Not absorption — utilization. Peptides absorb regardless, but need C to form functional skin collagen.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can vitamin C replace collagen?</summary><p>No. Vitamin C is the tool; collagen peptides are the materials. Need both for skin synthesis.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What foods have vitamin C?</summary><p>Red pepper (95mg), orange (70mg), kiwi (64mg), strawberries (49mg), broccoli, citrus.</p></details>
